description: Worldwide Vintage Autos is pleased to present this 1972 Ford Bronco 4x4. THIS IS THE BRONCO YOU WANT! Restored, power brakes, 302 V8, uncut, red, etc. A dream come true!   HISTORY  The original Bronco was an ORV (Off-Road Vehicle), intended to compete primarily with Jeep CJ models and the International Harvester Scout. The Bronco's small size riding on a 92-inch (2,337 mm) wheelbase made it maneuverable for some uses, but impractical as a tow vehicle. The Bronco was Ford's first compact SUV.  The idea behind the Bronco began with Ford product manager Donald N. Frey, who also conceived the Ford Mustang; and similarly, Lee Iacocca pushed the idea through into production. In many ways, the Bronco was a more original concept than the Mustang; whereas the Mustang was based upon the Ford Falcon, the Bronco had a frame, suspension, and a body that were not shared with any other vehicle. description: For sale in our Indianapolis Showroom is a 1957 Ford Thunderbird. The Thunderbird created a market niche that eventually became known as the personal luxury car.The Ford Thunderbird began life in February 1953 in direct response to Chevrolet's new sports car, the Corvette, which was publicly unveiled in prototype form just a month before. Under rapid development, the Thunderbird went from idea to prototype in about a year, being unveiled to the public at the Detroit Auto Show on February 20, 1954. It was a two-seat design available with a detachable glass-fibre hard top and a folding fabric top. Production of the Thunderbird began later on in 1954 on September 9 with the car beginning sales as a 1955 model on October 22, 1954. Though sharing some design characteristics with other Fords of the time, such as single, circular headlamps and tail lamps and modest tailfins, the Thunderbird was sleeker and more athletic in shape, and had features like a hood scoop and a 150 mph  speedometer hinting a higher performance nature that other Fords didn't possess.This 1957 Thunderbird has Starmist Blue Paint with a matching two tone interior. It also has a navy blue soft top and a Starmist Blue Hard top with Stand. This car has aftermarket AC that blows cold. This beatuy is powered by 312 cubic inch motor with a 3 speed transmision. The engine was rebuilt just over 2,000 miles ago. The 1957 Thunderbird is also equipped with Wipers, Power Steering, Seat belts,and  Leather Seats. This is a great example of a period correct Tbird that has won many shows. Car has documentation of maintence that the owner has completed over several years. If your looking for a 1950s Thunderbird that has been loved and well cared for this is the one.  This 1957 Ford Thunderbird for sale is located in our Indianapolis Showroom and can be seen in greater detail, including a High Def video at www.GatewayClassicCars.com. Please call (317)688-1100 or email us at INDY@gatewayclassiccars.com for additional information.

description: As Lee Iacocca's assistant general manager and chief engineer, Donald N. Frey was the head engineer for the Mustang project - supervising the development of the Mustang in a record 18 months from September 1962 to March 1964 - while Iacocca himself championed the project as Ford Division general manager. One of the design requirements established by Ford for this Mustang was that it should be a 4-passenger car and this has been neatly accomplished while still retaining much of the ''coupe'' look. The 1966 Mustang debuted with moderate trim changes including a new grille, side ornamentation, wheel covers and gas cap. Ford's new C-4 ''cruise-o-matic'' three-speed auto transmission also became available for the 225 hp V8. This '66 Mustang Hardtop has lots of appeal, from it long, low lines to its recognizable engine growl it's what made this ''America's Favorite Fun Car''. There is plenty of room for the driver to get into the Mustang, the door being well placed in this respect, the bucket seats are above average and the shift lever is within comfortable reach. We're offering this 1966 Ford Mustang Hardtop adorned in RED over BLACK VINYL. This classic comes with $472 (in 1966) dollars in Extra Charge options including the CRUISE-O-MATIC 3-SPEED AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION, 289CID-2V 200HP V-8 ENGINE, POWER STEERING, RADIO & ANTENNA, TINTED GLASS WINDSHIELD, 2-SPEED ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS & DAY/NIGHT REARVIEW MIRROR. Plus these aftermarket add-ons/upgrades DUAL EXHAUST, DISC BRAKES, CHROME AIR FILTER, CHROME VALVE COVERS, CHROME VALVE COVER BREATHER, CHROME OIL DIPSTICK, ALUMINUM RADIATOR, 14 INCH WHEELS, ''PREMIER'' REAR SPEAKERS, RED EXTERIOR PAINT. This vehicle also includes 1 set of keys and rubber floor mats. Comes comprehensively serviced and detailed by our highly regarded Bosch Authorized Service Facility. Trades Welcome.

Garrett Classics is proud to showcase this incredible find, a one-family owned 1964 1/2 Ford Mustang that was purchased new at John Meyers Courtesy Ford in Garland, Texas. This Mustang would remain in the area to this day. Currently it is proudly displayed & for sale on our showroom floor in Lewisville, Texas. This is a true early production car built May 12th, 1964, ordered in Raven Black and optioned with the 260 2bbl. V8. Enjoy our presentation and feel free to contact Dave at 214-213-7072 or Maris at 214-616-2317 with any questions.

The body displays it's original paint of Raven Black . The paint has some flaws and is showing age, but still cleans up and presents well, as you can see in these photos. There was one minor scratch and dent on the rear passenger side that was touched up years ago, but other than that the paint is original. The doors, hood, and deck lid align correctly. The glass is in good condition and the wheels are original along with the wheel covers. The tires are very old whitewall poly-bias all around.
The owners of the car  won several awards over the years at Mustang Club of America shows, for original car.

The car is as close to all original as you can get. It is a true survivor. Someone can enjoy keeping the car original and continuing to show it, or upgrade it a bit and have a wonderful solid 64 1/2  Mustang to enjoy.
The interior shows very well. The instrument cluster is original and in great shape. The mileage of 26,136 is correct to the car. It drives and handles as such.

The car has had some mechanical work, recently the fuel tank replaced, and the clutch was replaced in 2006 and the flywheel resurfaced at that time. The engine runs very good and is paired with a 3-speed manual transmission, also stock spec for this car. It is still using the correct generator charging system and is optioned with air conditioning (complete & needs service). The firewall, inner fenders, and core support is straight, while the inner fender stamping matches the VIN.
The undercarriage is in very good condition front to back.
The trunk features the correct spare/jack and mat.
Again feel free to contact Dave at 214-213-7072 or Maris at 214-616-2317 with any questions.

description: The 1977 Ford Thunderbird was a drastic departure from the previous generation. Rather than continuing to grow, the Thunderbird, like much of the domestic product line, shrunk in size as a response to growing concerns about fuel costs. The car was nearly 1,000 pounds lighter than the 1976 model, and rode on a wheelbase that was 6 inches shorter. In addition to size, the 1977-79â€™ Thunderbirdâ€™s price was reduced as well, now with a $5,000 base price. The car was still Fordâ€™s entrant in the â€œpersonal luxury carâ€ market, however, despite the smaller package.The Thunderbirdâ€™s new look was similar in spirit to earlier models, only now it featured concealed headlights, a more square grille, and a glassier cabin, with opera windows.The carâ€™s 302-cid, 130-hp V-8 was standard and 149- and 161-hp versions of the 351-cid V-8 were optional. Regardless of engine choice, shifting was managed by a three-speed automatic transmission. This particular example is equipped with the optional 351 V8 and has optional Factory Air Conditioning. The car hails from Arizona where it has only been driven 30,803 since new. From the outside to the inside, every corner of this Thunderbrid is absolutely impeccable. The original owner took extremely good car of his Thunderbird and did not let her go until 2 years ago. We also have all the original paper work for the car including Protect-o-Plate, Warranty Car, Sales Receipt and Ownersâ€™ Manual. Overall, the car is in superb condition and belongs in a museum. For more information or to make an offer, give Austin a call at 863-226-8590.
